(Kf)(x)=\large\int_0^1(1+xt)f(t)dt
(Kf)(x)=\large\int_0^1(1+xt)f(t)dt=\large\int_0^1f(t)dt+x\large\int_0^1tf(t)dt
a=\large\int_0^1f(t)dt
b=\large\int_0^1tf(t)dt
(Kf)(x)=a+bx
Kf=\mu f
f
\frac{a+bx}{\mu}=f(x)
a=\int_0^1 f(t)dt=\int_0^1\frac{a+bt}{\mu}dt=\frac{a}{\mu}\int_0^1dt+\frac{b}{\mu}\int_0^1tdt=\frac{a}{\mu}+\frac{b}{2\mu}
a(1-\frac{1}{\mu})-b(\frac{1}{2\mu})=0
b=\int_0^1tf(t)=\int_0^1t(\frac{a+bt}{\mu})dt=\frac{a}{\mu}\int_0^1tdt+\frac{b}{\mu}\int_0^1t^2dt=\frac{a}{2\mu}+\frac{b}{3\mu}
\implies a(\frac{-1}{2\mu})+b(1-\frac{1}{3\mu})=0
\begin{cases} a(1-\frac{1}{\mu})-b(\frac{1}{2\mu})=0   \\ a(\frac{-1}{2\mu})+b(1-\frac{1}{3\mu})=0   \\ \end{cases}
\mu=0,\frac{2}{3}\pm \frac{\sqrt{13}}{6}
